com.apriori.collections

Class AbstractLinkedImmutableList<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.apriori.collections.AbstractImmutableCollection<E>
      • com.apriori.collections.AbstractLinkedImmutableList<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - the type of element in the list
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    ImmutableCollection<E>, ImmutableList<E>, SizedIterable<E>, Iterable<E>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractLinkedImmutableList.LinkedSubList

    public abstract class AbstractLinkedImmutableList<E>
extends AbstractImmutableCollection<E>
implements ImmutableList<E>
    An abstract base class for ImmutableList implementations that use linked data structures so that access is sequential. Random access operations in this sort of list have linear runtime complexity. Sub-classes need only implement SizedIterable.size(), ImmutableList.first(), and ImmutableList.rest().

      • indexOf

        public int indexOf(Object o)
        Description copied from interface: ImmutableList
        Finds the first occurrence of the specified element in the list and returns the corresponding index. The search starts at the beginning of the list, and the index of the first matching element is returned. If no match is found then -1 is returned. A matching item is one that is equal to the specified item. If the specified item is null then a null in the list is a match. Otherwise, an item in the list that equals the specified object is a match.

        Description copied from interface: ImmutableList
        Returns true if this list is equal to the specified object. The objects are equal if both of them are ImmutableLists and they contain the same elements in the same order. So they are equal if both lists are the same size and if, for every index i, the item at index i in this list is equal to the item at index i in the given list.
